WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:02.294
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

00:02.294 --> 00:04.171
Ugh, that dress is awful.

00:04.171 --> 00:05.797
Construction is so shoddy.

00:05.797 --> 00:09.009
Yeah, but the design
is really fashion forward.

00:09.009 --> 00:11.010
Look at that draping.

00:11.594 --> 00:14.514
That's right,
I said "draping."

00:14.514 --> 00:16.308
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

00:17.434 --> 00:19.144
Hey, guys.
Hey.

00:19.144 --> 00:21.688
I need to borrow a book
a guy would like.

00:21.688 --> 00:22.439
JEFF:
Is it for Adam?

00:22.439 --> 00:25.900
'Cause we don't have anything
that pops up.

00:25.900 --> 00:27.735
No. It's for my new friend,
Charlie.

00:27.735 --> 00:29.821
I started volunteering
to read to the elderly.

00:29.821 --> 00:32.032
Really? What made you
start doing that?

00:32.032 --> 00:34.409
Was it court ordered?
A little glug, glug?

00:34.409 --> 00:36.703
Little pow, pow?

00:38.496 --> 00:40.873
Why do so many
of the titles start with

00:40.873 --> 00:42.834
The Big Bathroom Book of?

00:42.834 --> 00:44.377
I find the Triple B series

00:44.377 --> 00:47.214
to be entertaining
and succinct.

00:47.214 --> 00:49.757
I will go with a novel
since I won't be reading

00:49.757 --> 00:50.800
to Charlie in the bathroom.

00:50.800 --> 00:53.678
If he's wearing a diaper,
every room's the bathroom.

00:53.678 --> 00:57.807
It's the thing Jeff most looks
forward to about getting old.

00:57.807 --> 01:00.185
Well, it's good to have goals.

01:00.185 --> 01:02.145
See you guys later.

01:02.145 --> 01:04.314
So Jen's off helping others

01:04.314 --> 01:06.608
while we're spending
our Saturday in sweats,

01:06.608 --> 01:09.277
watching mindless TV
and eating kids cereal

01:09.277 --> 01:11.279
right out of the box.Yeah.

01:11.279 --> 01:13.240
We win.

01:15.075 --> 01:17.577
I have all day.

01:18.411 --> 01:20.205
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S "HOW MANY WAYS"
PLAYING]

01:20.205 --> 01:25.042
♪♪ How many ways
To say, "I love you?" ♪♪

01:25.293 --> 01:30.215
♪♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared? ♪♪

01:30.215 --> 01:32.967
♪♪ With you by my side ♪♪

01:32.967 --> 01:34.886
♪♪ There is no denyin' ♪♪

01:34.886 --> 01:39.307
♪♪ I can't wait
For me and you ♪♪

01:41.184 --> 01:43.645
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

01:45.104 --> 01:47.440
Hey, I--

01:47.440 --> 01:50.110
What is that smell?
Are you wearing cologne?

01:50.110 --> 01:51.027
Cologne? Please.

01:51.027 --> 01:52.737
It's pheromones
from a bull moose

01:52.737 --> 01:54.406
in rutting season,
dip wipe.

01:54.406 --> 01:57.992
Yeah, 'cause you're interviewing
for a new assistant today.

01:57.992 --> 01:59.869
Yeah. That last one
was such a whiner.

01:59.869 --> 02:00.953
I was tired
of all her questions.

02:00.953 --> 02:03.956
Well, "where am I?" and
"how long I've been out for?"

02:03.956 --> 02:05.125
are legitimate questions.

02:05.125 --> 02:08.503
Well, that's water and hush
money under the bridge.

02:08.503 --> 02:10.922
So how's it looking
out there?

02:10.922 --> 02:12.465
Is the casting couch
filling up?

02:12.465 --> 02:14.801
Oh, take a look for yourself.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.600
Dude,
what's with the meat locker?

02:22.600 --> 02:26.271
Oh. Remember? You're not allowed
to hire women anymore.

02:26.271 --> 02:26.979
What? Why?

02:26.979 --> 02:28.940
Didn't you get
the 15-page reprimand

02:28.940 --> 02:31.234
hand-delivered
by company attorneys?

02:31.234 --> 02:34.111
I thought that was a joke.

02:34.111 --> 02:36.198
What am I gonna do
with a male assistant?

02:36.198 --> 02:37.365
What do you do
with a female assistant?

02:37.365 --> 02:39.784
I don't know. Sniff their hair,
tell 'em to bend over

02:39.784 --> 02:43.288
and pick stuff up.
It's all in the reprimand.

02:43.288 --> 02:46.666
Now I smell like moose whiz
for nothing.

02:46.666 --> 02:48.125
I don't even know
how to pick a guy.

02:48.125 --> 02:51.045
My normal interview questions
don't apply.

02:51.921 --> 02:54.006
All right. "Question one:

02:54.006 --> 02:57.051
Can I get you a cocktail?"

02:57.051 --> 02:59.637
I don't like to drink alone.

02:59.637 --> 03:02.515
Oh, my God. You actually
ask them the second question?

03:02.515 --> 03:05.518
Well, presumably
they've had a cocktail.

03:05.518 --> 03:11.065
Let's just start the
interviewing. Who's up first?

03:11.065 --> 03:12.609
MAN:
Ow!

03:12.609 --> 03:14.986
You. Come on in.

03:14.986 --> 03:17.364
Mr. Dunbar.
It's an honor to meet you.

03:17.364 --> 03:20.032
Here's my resume.
And your bagel.

03:20.032 --> 03:21.909
Timmy, huh?

03:21.909 --> 03:23.245
Did that bagel
hit the ground?

03:23.245 --> 03:26.831
No, just me.
Great. You're hired.

03:26.831 --> 03:28.458
Uh, Russell.

03:28.458 --> 03:31.461
What? He caught the bagel.

03:32.837 --> 03:35.298
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

03:37.425 --> 03:38.593
Hey.
Hey.

03:38.593 --> 03:41.929
Get this. Guy on the elevator
just tried talking to me.

03:41.929 --> 03:45.767
Just shut up
and look at the numbers.

03:45.767 --> 03:47.935
Hi.
Hi.

03:47.935 --> 03:49.103
What's all this crap?

03:49.103 --> 03:51.606
Last night
I had an epiphany.

03:51.606 --> 03:54.734
I'm surprised,
it wasn't even my A game.

03:54.734 --> 03:55.735
No. I don't mean that,

03:55.735 --> 03:59.196
Although that would be
an epiphany too.

03:59.196 --> 04:00.990
No. Jen's volunteering
made me realize

04:00.990 --> 04:03.701
I don't do anything
to help other people.

04:03.701 --> 04:06.162
You didn't know that?

04:06.162 --> 04:08.164
I want to do more.

04:08.164 --> 04:08.998
So I got the number from Jen

04:08.998 --> 04:11.751
and I signed up to read
to the elderly too.

04:11.751 --> 04:14.254
Oh. Here we go.

04:14.254 --> 04:15.087
What does that mean?

04:15.087 --> 04:16.923
Well, You have a habit
of getting on these

04:16.923 --> 04:18.800
"I'm gonna be
a better person" kicks.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.009
And you always
end up quitting

04:20.009 --> 04:22.429
and then feeling bad
about yourself.

04:22.429 --> 04:25.097
I do not always quit.

04:25.097 --> 04:27.267
Really?
Being a vegetarian,

04:27.267 --> 04:29.269
reducing your carbon footprint,

04:29.269 --> 04:30.687
meditating.
Hey!

04:30.687 --> 04:32.480
It was hard to meditate
with you

04:32.480 --> 04:35.692
constantly trying
to feel me up.

04:36.484 --> 04:39.321
Well, you were just
sitting there.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.448
This time is gonna be
different.

04:41.448 --> 04:43.866
No. No, it isn't.

04:43.866 --> 04:44.659
Yes. Yes, it is.

04:44.659 --> 04:47.620
This time I'm committed
to helping an actual person.

04:47.620 --> 04:50.665
Tell you what. If I'm wrong,
I will volunteer too.

04:50.665 --> 04:52.667
But if I'm right
and you quit,

04:52.667 --> 04:57.088
you owe me one
"Jeff's Choice."

04:57.672 --> 04:59.299
If you don't think
you can do it...

04:59.299 --> 05:00.800
All right, all right,
you're on.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.969
But trust me,
you're going down.

05:02.969 --> 05:05.638
No, no. I said
"Jeff's Choice."

05:05.638 --> 05:08.140
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

05:11.268 --> 05:12.812
Hey, where's Timmy?

05:12.812 --> 05:14.939
He's off doing
some assistant work.

05:14.939 --> 05:18.735
Kid's got a sharp mind,
he's a real go-getter.

05:19.319 --> 05:22.822
Okay, sir, I just finished
alphabetizing your erotica.

05:22.822 --> 05:23.698
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

05:23.698 --> 05:25.700
Above and beyond, I like that.

05:25.700 --> 05:28.411
Seriously? You've got an MBA.
No. No, it's fine.

05:28.411 --> 05:30.162
One must start
at the bottom.

05:30.162 --> 05:32.665
A rule clearly followed
by many of the actors

05:32.665 --> 05:35.001
in your film collection.

05:36.210 --> 05:37.420
However,
I did have some thoughts

05:37.420 --> 05:39.672
about the Brooklyn Shipyard
redevelopment--

05:39.672 --> 05:40.548
Yeah, and I wanna hear 'em.

05:40.548 --> 05:43.009
But, quickly, can you just do
that thing for Adam?

05:43.009 --> 05:46.971
Really, sir, I don't--
Come on. It's fun.

05:49.432 --> 05:53.185
Bond. James Bond.

05:54.061 --> 05:55.647
Never gets old.

05:55.647 --> 05:57.231
Debatable, sir.

05:57.231 --> 06:00.735
Well, I'm off to, uh,
pick up your prescriptions,

06:00.735 --> 06:02.069
your dry cleaning,

06:02.069 --> 06:04.030
and two giant gumballs
from the machine

06:04.030 --> 06:05.197
in the Times Square arcade.

06:05.197 --> 06:08.200
Yeah. And don't you quit
till you get a red one.

06:08.200 --> 06:08.910
Naturally, sir.

06:08.910 --> 06:11.538
Mr. Rhodes? Would you like
a giant gumball as well?

06:11.538 --> 06:15.833
No, Timmy, I am not gonna make
you get me a stupid gumball.

06:15.833 --> 06:17.168
Thank you, sir.

06:17.168 --> 06:19.003
Unless they have
the speckled kind.

06:19.003 --> 06:20.797
I'll take one of those.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.090
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

06:23.090 --> 06:26.844
"Her bosom heaved as Lance
whispered softly in her ear--"

06:26.844 --> 06:27.554
WOMAN:
What?

06:27.554 --> 06:32.600
"H-Her bosom heaved--"
Speak up!

06:33.601 --> 06:37.772
"Her bosom heaved
as Lance--

06:37.772 --> 06:39.106
[COUGHING]

06:39.106 --> 06:41.943
Take a lozenge.
Thank you.

06:41.943 --> 06:44.236
Oh, God,
there's hair on them.

06:46.322 --> 06:48.575
[SIGHS]

06:52.161 --> 06:53.455
All right, where were we?

06:53.455 --> 06:57.459
Don't let me interrupt you.
I just have to...

06:57.459 --> 06:58.334
I should step out.

06:58.334 --> 07:02.129
No, no. Sit down.
Keep reading!

07:02.129 --> 07:04.549
Keep reading!

07:05.467 --> 07:08.511
"It's a dream being here
with you."

07:08.511 --> 07:10.472
"I Hope this...

07:10.472 --> 07:13.558
magical moment never--"
Be careful!

07:13.558 --> 07:16.185
NURSE: Oh, no. No!
[THUDDING]

07:16.185 --> 07:19.146
Steven, get a mop!

07:20.356 --> 07:22.817
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

07:25.236 --> 07:25.737
Well,

07:25.737 --> 07:29.198
if it isn't
Leonardo DiCaprio

07:29.198 --> 07:31.701
and theTitanic.

07:33.661 --> 07:34.537
Who's this guy?

07:34.537 --> 07:36.330
This is Russell's new assistant,
Timmy.

07:36.330 --> 07:40.835
You got me,
I-I do look like Leo.

07:41.335 --> 07:43.295
So where's Russell?
Running late, sir.

07:43.295 --> 07:45.673
Would you mind sitting next
to Mr. Bingham?

07:45.673 --> 07:48.425
Mr. Dunbar likes to see both
of your reactions

07:48.425 --> 07:51.262
to his hilarity.

07:51.262 --> 07:54.348
Seriously, who is this guy?

07:54.348 --> 07:57.059
Well, see you guys
met Timmy.

07:57.059 --> 07:57.810
[CHUCKLES]

07:57.810 --> 07:59.896
So, what'd you go with?
Leo and Titanic, sir.

07:59.896 --> 08:03.232
Cut them to the core,
just as you predicted.

08:03.232 --> 08:05.693
By the way, we have
a 3:00 meeting with--

08:05.693 --> 08:08.112
Oh, all business matters
go through Timmy.

08:08.112 --> 08:10.239
Timmy,
would you tell Russell--

08:10.239 --> 08:14.243
I'm sorry,
Mr. Dunbar's at lunch.

08:14.243 --> 08:15.411
He's right there!

08:15.411 --> 08:18.623
We'll call back.
Where can we reach you?

08:18.623 --> 08:21.250
I'm right here.

08:21.250 --> 08:23.169
What's this?
We haven't even ordered yet.

08:23.169 --> 08:26.964
I called in ahead. So, sir,
saltines, oyster crackers?

08:26.964 --> 08:30.301
Surprise me.

08:30.301 --> 08:33.387
Ooh, check her out.

08:33.846 --> 08:35.932
Would you like me to pursue
that opportunity

08:35.932 --> 08:37.266
and obtain her contact
information?

08:37.266 --> 08:40.102
While you enjoy your soup?
You would do that for me?

08:40.102 --> 08:41.270
If you would take a look
at my idea

08:41.270 --> 08:44.065
for the Brooklyn Shipyard
project. You did say you would.

08:44.065 --> 08:46.358
Oh, yeah, yeah.
I will, okay, I promise.

08:46.358 --> 08:49.028
Then it'll be my pleasure.

08:49.028 --> 08:52.031
SpongeBob, squarehead.

08:55.785 --> 08:58.245
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

08:59.038 --> 09:01.708
So you don't love reading
to the elderly,

09:01.708 --> 09:03.167
it's not the end
of the world.

09:03.167 --> 09:05.670
This is nothing
like I expected.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.463
I mean, she is almost deaf.

09:07.463 --> 09:09.173
I am not reading
to the elderly,

09:09.173 --> 09:10.633
I'm screaming at them!

09:10.633 --> 09:13.427
You're screaming at me.
Oh, what does it matter?

09:13.427 --> 09:16.848
We're the only people
who can hear in this place.

09:16.848 --> 09:18.432
Look,
I've been doing this awhile.

09:18.432 --> 09:20.267
so I know how difficult
it can be.

09:20.267 --> 09:21.978
Well, I can't quit.

09:21.978 --> 09:22.895
Then I'd have to face Jeff.

09:22.895 --> 09:24.939
He thinks it's just
another one of my "kicks."

09:24.939 --> 09:27.358
Oh, like when you were gonna
start walking to work,

09:27.358 --> 09:30.152
or read more, or stop
drinking so much wine...

09:30.152 --> 09:32.196
Boy, you'd think
with all your volunteering

09:32.196 --> 09:34.281
you wouldn't have had time
to make a list.

09:34.281 --> 09:36.283
Anyway, if I quit,
he's gonna do his

09:36.283 --> 09:39.453
"I was right and you were wrong"
dance which, surprise,

09:39.453 --> 09:41.455
is performed in the nude.

09:43.499 --> 09:44.959
Jennifer, my dear,
there you are.

09:44.959 --> 09:49.005
Oh, hey! Audrey,
this is Charlie.

09:49.005 --> 09:50.715
A pleasure to meet you.

09:50.715 --> 09:53.050
You're kidding?

09:53.050 --> 09:54.468
This is who you got?

09:54.468 --> 09:56.804
I know,
isn't he adorable?

09:56.804 --> 09:58.139
No, you're adorable.

09:58.139 --> 10:00.141
Ha, ha.
Oh, Charlie.

10:00.141 --> 10:01.017
[LAUGHS]

10:01.017 --> 10:03.519
Today he's reading to me.

10:03.519 --> 10:04.311
Is he?
JENNIFER: Mm-hm.

10:04.311 --> 10:07.732
I thought we'd do so
while having lunch outside.

10:07.732 --> 10:09.400
My dear.

10:09.400 --> 10:11.694
Hang in there.

10:12.820 --> 10:15.447
In there.

10:16.157 --> 10:18.618
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

10:20.662 --> 10:23.122
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

10:27.126 --> 10:30.087
I got Timmy out in the plaza
scoping chicks for me.

10:30.087 --> 10:33.883
Timmy, see the girl in the tall
boots by the hot dog cart?

10:33.883 --> 10:35.092
You got her. Yeah.

10:35.092 --> 10:36.969
See if she's single.

10:36.969 --> 10:38.971
Oh, she has a boyfriend?

10:38.971 --> 10:41.348
Uh, see if she wants to get back
at him for anything.

10:41.348 --> 10:44.268
D-Don't you think you're taking
advantage of Timmy?

10:44.268 --> 10:47.604
Taking advantage
or mentoring?

10:47.604 --> 10:49.565
Taking advantage.

10:49.565 --> 10:51.984
Or mentoring.

10:51.984 --> 10:55.571
Saying it slower
doesn't make it true.

10:55.571 --> 10:57.990
Timmy, girl in pink sweater
across the--

10:57.990 --> 11:01.327
Oh. Oh, he hit a hot dog cart.

11:01.327 --> 11:02.995
Timmy, you down?

11:02.995 --> 11:05.665
Listen, if you can move.

11:05.665 --> 11:09.168
Get me a hot dog
with mustard and relish.

11:09.501 --> 11:12.755
So, what are you saying, you
don't want to volunteer anymore?

11:12.755 --> 11:14.465
Oh, no, no, no, no,
I am not quitting.

11:14.465 --> 11:18.302
I can't quit. Or my husband--
Are you married?

11:18.302 --> 11:20.221
No, I don't need that.

11:20.221 --> 11:22.932
Well, it's just that,
you know, since I'm new,

11:22.932 --> 11:26.435
maybe there's a patient
who's a little less challenging.

11:26.435 --> 11:28.562
Actually, we assigned you Edie
because you're new.

11:28.562 --> 11:31.315
Most of our other residents
have far more difficult issues.

11:31.315 --> 11:35.444
Are you kidding me?
Her room is like a monkey cage.

11:35.444 --> 11:38.530
I'm sorry,
it's just...

11:38.530 --> 11:41.951
I was hoping maybe
I could get somebody...

11:41.951 --> 11:44.036
like Charlie, for example.

11:44.036 --> 11:46.330
Charlie already has a volunteer.

11:46.330 --> 11:47.164
We could trade.

11:47.164 --> 11:49.792
I don't think we could do that.

11:49.792 --> 11:50.835
Maybe we can.

11:50.835 --> 11:54.171
Say, Charlie in exchange for...

11:54.171 --> 11:56.215
Andrew Jackson?

12:01.804 --> 12:04.306
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

12:05.557 --> 12:07.810
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

12:07.810 --> 12:09.186
Oh, hey.

12:09.186 --> 12:12.731
So how was your picnic
with Jay Gatsby?

12:12.731 --> 12:15.609
Why should I tell you,
geezer thief?

12:15.609 --> 12:17.736
What are you talking about? I--
Save it.

12:17.736 --> 12:20.531
Miss Alberts told me about
your lame bribe attempt.

12:20.531 --> 12:24.118
Damn it.
I should've gone with a 50.

12:24.118 --> 12:25.744
I'm sorry,
I was desperate.

12:25.744 --> 12:28.831
I'm just gonna have to tell Jeff
he was right and face the music.

12:28.831 --> 12:31.876
And the disturbing dance
that goes with it.

12:31.876 --> 12:35.712
Or you could buck up and realize
you're comforting someone

12:35.712 --> 12:38.465
who probably doesn't have
much longer to live.

12:38.465 --> 12:41.803
You're right.

12:42.845 --> 12:45.431
You're right.

12:49.685 --> 12:52.396
[DOOR CLOSES]
Hey.

12:52.396 --> 12:54.731
[SIGHS]

13:00.988 --> 13:03.365
[SNIFFLING]

13:05.827 --> 13:09.246
What, you got a cold?

13:09.246 --> 13:11.415
No. I'm sad, Jeff.

13:11.415 --> 13:15.336
Don't worry,
it's just a cold.

13:16.087 --> 13:19.506
I'm sad because...

13:19.506 --> 13:23.635
my dear friend Edie,
she...

13:23.635 --> 13:25.972
This is hard.

13:29.766 --> 13:32.728
[SOBBING]

13:32.728 --> 13:35.772
Edie passed away.

13:37.524 --> 13:39.568
She passed away? When?

13:39.568 --> 13:40.569
Today.

13:40.569 --> 13:43.990
With me right there
at her bedside.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.950
[SIGHS]

13:45.950 --> 13:47.826
Really?
Yeah.

13:47.826 --> 13:49.828
I just finished
the day's reading and...

13:49.828 --> 13:54.250
and she reached out
and I took her hand, and...

13:54.250 --> 13:56.878
this part just blew me away.

13:56.878 --> 13:59.964
She smiled and whispered,

13:59.964 --> 14:03.592
"thank you, kind angel."

14:06.678 --> 14:09.598
And then she was gone.

14:09.598 --> 14:12.601
Oh.
It was a powerful moment.

14:12.601 --> 14:14.186
[SOBBING]

14:15.312 --> 14:16.397
So...

14:16.397 --> 14:17.398
[SNIFFLES]

14:17.398 --> 14:21.027
I guess our bet is off.

14:22.444 --> 14:23.820
[SIGHS]

14:23.820 --> 14:27.699
Edie called
five minutes ago.

14:29.911 --> 14:33.830
You left your sunglasses.

14:34.831 --> 14:37.126
What?

14:37.126 --> 14:38.752
Wow!

14:40.004 --> 14:43.257
She was only sleeping!

14:43.257 --> 14:45.634
[SIGHING]

14:46.135 --> 14:51.682
What a relief!
This is wonderful news!

14:53.184 --> 14:55.186
That's what
you're going with?

14:55.186 --> 14:56.603
Yes.

14:56.603 --> 14:59.065
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

15:02.359 --> 15:03.694
Not to be a pest, sir,

15:03.694 --> 15:06.280
but have you had an opportunity
to look over my proposal yet?

15:06.280 --> 15:09.033
You know what I haven't,
but it's on my to do list.

15:09.033 --> 15:11.160
I keep your to do list, sir.
Oh.

15:11.160 --> 15:13.620
Okay.
Why don't you take lunch?

15:13.620 --> 15:14.914
Yes.
Mmm.

15:14.914 --> 15:18.292
Oh, hey, kettle corn. Whoo-ooh.
[CHUCKLES]

15:18.292 --> 15:19.501
That's a good batch.

15:19.501 --> 15:21.670
Mm. You know,
this would be a great cereal.

15:21.670 --> 15:23.714
Pour some milk in a bowl.
You want to?

15:23.714 --> 15:26.258
You want me to get bowls?
Oh.

15:26.258 --> 15:28.135
All right then,
see you in ten minutes.

15:28.135 --> 15:29.470
Bye, bye.
Who was that?

15:29.470 --> 15:32.014
Oh, after I ran
into the hot dog cart,

15:32.014 --> 15:34.100
the girl in the pink sweater
helped me up.

15:34.100 --> 15:35.142
My girl in the pink sweater?

15:35.142 --> 15:37.811
Yes. We got to talking,
made lunch plans.

15:37.811 --> 15:41.232
Timmy, can you close
the door for a second? Ahem.

15:41.232 --> 15:46.028
Timmy, are you familiar
with Dunbar Company Policy?

15:46.028 --> 15:48.864
Every word, sir.

15:48.864 --> 15:50.032
Okay. Well...

15:50.032 --> 15:53.744
I'm gonna guess that they're
pretty strict about conducting

15:53.744 --> 15:55.912
personal business
on company time.

15:55.912 --> 15:58.665
Quite frankly,
I am very disappointed in you.

15:58.665 --> 15:59.416
I'm sorry, Mr. Dunbar,

15:59.416 --> 16:02.669
I felt since I'd accumulated
so many numbers for you--

16:02.669 --> 16:04.463
For me? Oh, right, for me,

16:04.463 --> 16:06.007
because you work for me.
Yes.

16:06.007 --> 16:08.134
And I've done everything
you've asked of me,

16:08.134 --> 16:10.261
including things
I find quite unsavory.

16:10.261 --> 16:13.597
He's talking about
all the porn.

16:13.597 --> 16:15.891
Yes, thank you.

16:15.891 --> 16:18.602
Now, sir, I realize
I have to pay my dues,

16:18.602 --> 16:21.397
but I don't feel
that I'm being taken seriously.

16:21.397 --> 16:24.316
Can I try on your glasses?
No!

16:24.316 --> 16:26.360
I cannot continue
to be your assistant

16:26.360 --> 16:28.695
if there's no chance
for professional advancement.

16:28.695 --> 16:31.198
You will find my resignation
on your desk in the morning,

16:31.198 --> 16:33.534
along with your final hot
Croissan'Wich.

16:33.534 --> 16:34.826
Timmy, don't go.

16:34.826 --> 16:37.997
You're right. I've been remiss.
I tell you what.

16:37.997 --> 16:40.416
I'm gonna read your report
right now.

16:40.416 --> 16:42.251
Where is that report?
It was right--

16:42.251 --> 16:44.586
No. You stuck it under
the table leg here

16:44.586 --> 16:47.298
so it wouldn't wobble.

16:47.298 --> 16:47.923
No, no, no.

16:47.923 --> 16:50.301
I didn't put the report under
so won't wobble.

16:50.301 --> 16:55.347
I put the table on the report
so wouldn't blow away.

16:55.347 --> 16:59.310
How stupid
do you think I am, sir?

16:59.310 --> 17:04.106
I mean, you're clearly,
clearly, taking advantage of me.

17:04.106 --> 17:06.192
Taking advantage or mentoring?

17:06.192 --> 17:07.401
What?

17:07.401 --> 17:10.404
Or mentoring.

17:10.404 --> 17:13.990
I suppose I hadn't thought
of it that way, sir.

17:13.990 --> 17:16.452
You gotta be kidding me.

17:16.452 --> 17:17.869
Why do you think I chose you?

17:17.869 --> 17:20.247
I assume because
I caught the bagel.

17:20.247 --> 17:22.333
No, no. I saw something in you.

17:22.333 --> 17:23.834
Something that made me think:

17:23.834 --> 17:25.169
"You're the guy."

17:25.169 --> 17:27.754
You could be the guy
that could shine.

17:27.754 --> 17:30.006
No, no.
Thrive at D-Dunbar Group.

17:30.006 --> 17:31.133
But you know, maybe I'm wrong.

17:31.133 --> 17:33.135
No, sir, you're not.
No, no. I'm wrong.

17:33.135 --> 17:35.846
You're not wrong at all.
I...

17:35.846 --> 17:37.931
Here's the thing.
Perhaps being...

17:37.931 --> 17:41.477
fresh out of Business School,
I was so focused on advancement,

17:41.477 --> 17:44.896
I did not recognize your
unconventional tutelage.

17:44.896 --> 17:46.773
No, Timmy, you didn't.

17:46.773 --> 17:48.567
And you know how that
made me feel?

17:48.567 --> 17:51.112
I guess I didn't take
into consideration--

17:51.112 --> 17:54.698
Bad, it made me feel bad.

17:54.698 --> 17:58.744
Now, lucky for you, I'm a big
believer in second chances.

17:58.744 --> 18:01.580
Oh, thank you, sir.
Thank you ever so much.

18:01.580 --> 18:03.332
I'll see you after lunch.

18:03.332 --> 18:04.250
Okay.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.252
Mr. Rhodes.

18:06.835 --> 18:12.299
I can't believe he bought
that mentoring crap.

18:13.008 --> 18:16.512
Or can you?

18:16.512 --> 18:19.431
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:19.431 --> 18:21.767
What happened?
Is it Edie?

18:21.767 --> 18:24.270
I'm very sorry
to tell you this,

18:24.270 --> 18:26.230
but Miss Bennett
passed away.

18:26.230 --> 18:31.235
She couldn't have done
this yesterday?

18:32.903 --> 18:33.945
Hey, you didn't happen to see

18:33.945 --> 18:36.532
a pair of sunglasses
in there, did you?

18:36.532 --> 18:38.992
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:41.328 --> 18:43.330
Hey. Shouldn't you be
at the home?

18:43.330 --> 18:45.457
You're not gonna
believe this,

18:45.457 --> 18:48.252
but Edie died.

18:48.252 --> 18:50.504
Really? No, uh,

18:50.504 --> 18:53.632
"thank you, kind angel"?

18:53.632 --> 18:56.051
It's not a joke, Jeff.

18:56.051 --> 18:58.137
She really died.
Huh.

18:58.137 --> 19:00.306
If she kicked one day sooner,

19:00.306 --> 19:02.891
you would've been
sitting pretty.

19:02.891 --> 19:07.062
Yeah. Trust me,
I did that math.

19:07.062 --> 19:07.896
But then I started to think

19:07.896 --> 19:12.901
that somehow, karmically,
this is my fault.

19:12.901 --> 19:14.403
Audrey--
No, really.

19:14.403 --> 19:17.948
When I was nine
I was so jealous of my sister.

19:17.948 --> 19:19.283
I wished
she would hurt her ankle

19:19.283 --> 19:22.994
so she wouldn't make
the pep squad. And she did.

19:22.994 --> 19:27.333
You pushed her
off the porch.

19:27.333 --> 19:28.167
You didn't...

19:28.167 --> 19:31.587
push Edie off the porch,
did you?

19:31.587 --> 19:33.922
No. But looks like you win.

19:33.922 --> 19:36.842
So nude up. Start dancing.
[SIGHS]

19:36.842 --> 19:39.636
The "I was right and you were
wrong" dance is no fun

19:39.636 --> 19:42.013
when you're already sad.

19:42.013 --> 19:44.183
I should just accept it.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.767
I am not a good person.

19:45.767 --> 19:47.769
Hey, don't say that.
You are a good person.

19:47.769 --> 19:50.564
Ah, I appreciate that
but it's not true.

19:50.564 --> 19:52.107
Sure it is. I mean,
who else out there

19:52.107 --> 19:53.984
would continue to try
and be better over

19:53.984 --> 19:56.695
and over again
without ever succeeding?

19:56.695 --> 19:59.240
And what do people
always tell children?

19:59.240 --> 20:01.325
It's not whether you win
or you lose,

20:01.325 --> 20:03.452
it's whether you try your best.

20:03.452 --> 20:05.746
And you always try your best.

20:05.746 --> 20:08.081
[CLICKING TONGUE]

20:08.081 --> 20:10.166
That is so sweet.

20:10.166 --> 20:11.627
Thank you.

20:11.627 --> 20:13.337
Feel better?
I do.

20:13.337 --> 20:14.588
A little less sad?

20:14.588 --> 20:17.716
Yeah.
Good.

20:17.716 --> 20:20.719
♪♪ I was right
And you were wrong ♪♪

20:20.719 --> 20:22.929
♪♪ Doo-dah, doo-dah ♪♪

20:22.929 --> 20:25.599
♪♪ I was right
And you were wrong ♪♪

20:25.599 --> 20:27.976
♪♪ All the doo-dah day ♪♪

20:27.976 --> 20:30.437
♪♪ Doo-dah-doo-dah-la ♪♪

20:30.437 --> 20:32.898
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:35.234 --> 20:36.568
What's up, Timmy?

20:36.568 --> 20:38.570
Mr. Rhodes.

20:43.492 --> 20:44.368
What the hell?

20:44.368 --> 20:46.370
I'm sorry, sir.
He's not in.

20:46.370 --> 20:48.289
Yes, he is.

20:48.289 --> 20:51.082
No, he's not.

20:51.082 --> 20:53.835
But I can see him.

20:54.711 --> 20:57.423
No, you can't.

20:59.758 --> 21:02.803
Would you care to leave
a number?

21:05.138 --> 21:07.599
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
